            <div>
               <ul>
                  <li>Purpose - Rainy Day is on a mission to make saving simple and accessible. You don’t have to be a financial expert to save money. Rainy Day is reliable and easy to use.</li>
                  <li>Objective - To design a tool that helps people save money quickly in preparation for a big purchase or expenditure.</li>
                  <li>Role - UX & UI Designer</li>
                  <li>Duration - Dec -Jan 2021/22</li>
               </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h2>My Process</h2>
            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/rainy day/rainyday_process@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/rainy day/rainyday_process@2x.png" alt="My Image" />  
               </picture>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h2>Research</h2>
            </div>
            <div>
               <ul>
                  <li>Goal - The goal of Rainy Day is to make saving money easier, especially for those who are new or inexperienced. It does this by providing personalized information/advice as well as keeping track of data.</li>
                  <li>Audience - This tool will help users who may need guidance in saving money or just want to keep track of their financial data.</li>
               </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h2>Ideation</h2>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h3>User Flow</h3>
               <p>This user flow details a user’s path through the app from opening the app to adding and editing a saving goal.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/rainy day/rainyday_user_flow@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/rainy day/rainyday_user_flow@1x.png" alt="My Image" />    
               </picture>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h3>Sketches</h3>
               <p>I created sketches for the screens using the user flow as a guide.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/rainy day/rainyday_sketches@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/rainy day/rainyday_sketches@2x.png" alt="My Image" />   
               </picture>
