               <h2>Wireframe</h2>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h4>Mid-Fidelity Wireframes</h4>
            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/rainy day/rainyday_wireframes@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/rainy day/rainyday_wireframes@2x.png" alt="My Image" />   
               </picture>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h3>Prototyping and User Testing</h3>
               <p>I created a prototype after finalizing styles for the wireframes. I had users attempt to accomplish several tasks in this prototype and recorded their feedback. This feedback was used to alleviate several notable pain points in the app.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/rainy day/rainyday_user_testing1@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/rainy day/rainyday_user_testing1@2x.png" alt="My Image" />
               </picture>
            </div>
            <div>
               <p>Pain Point #1 - Tester was confused by the “countdown” number for the remaining time in a goal. To make this more clear, I changed the “countdown” to be clearly labeled with “months” and “days” remaining.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/rainy day/rainyday_user_testing2@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/rainy day/rainyday_user_testing2@2x.png" alt="My Image" />  
               </picture>
            </div>
            <div>
               <p>Pain Point #2 -  User had trouble finding the “add funds” button. Adding funds is an important feature to a money saving app, so I changed this to a large button instead of a small arrow.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h2>Design</h2>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h3>Final Screens</h3>
               <p>After adjusting the design to remedy pain points identified through user testing, and applying any remaining styling, the final screens are completed.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <picture>
                  <source srcset="img/rainy day/rainyday_final_screens@1x.png" media="9max-width:767px)" />
                  <img src="img/rainy day/rainyday_final_screens@2x.png" alt="My Image" /> 
               </picture>
            </div>
            <div>
               <h2>Conclusion</h2>
               <p>I would like to add a lot more features and screens to this app in the future. I feel like I was only able to explore a few features in this app and would like to put more work into it. I would like to do more extensive user testing after adding these other features in order to keep the app user centered and easy to use.</p>
            </div>
